<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9992> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9992" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Poeneis et Siculeis. MRR I.212, Itgenshorst no. 139, Rich no. 138." ;
	dprr:hasID 9992 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7158> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7158" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 252. A milestone, discovered at Zaccharone in Sicily, on the road from Agrigentum to Panormus, with the inscription [C. Au]relius | [L. f.] Cotta | [C]onsol LVII, by A. di Vita (Kokalos 1, 1955, 10-21-AEpig. 1957, no. 172). Degrassi doubts so early a date, though he favors one not later than the second century and suggests that a later Cotta, perhaps L. Aurelius Cotta (98). Cos. 144, honored his ancestor in this way (Hommages a Albert Grenier 1.499-506). See now Degrassi ILLRP 1277, and Acta 5th Epig. Congress, Cambridge, 1967 169-170, with discussions cited there. Refer also to G. P. Verbrugghe, Itinera Romano, Bd. 2: Sicilia 19-23.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7158 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1232> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1232" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (name entire); Degrassi 44f., 117, 440f." ;
	dprr:hasID 1232 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1200> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1200" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (C. Aurelius C. f. C. n. Co[tta]), Degrassi 42f., 117, 438f.; cf. Jerome Chr. ad ann. 244, p. 132 Helm; and on Fabius, Liv. 23.22.10; Fabius' name must be supplied here in Fast. Cap. since all the other possible places are definitely known." ;
	dprr:hasID 1200 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1179> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1179" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Cic. Acad. 2.84; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.16; Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f. Both Consuls served in Sicily, besieging Lilybaeum and Drepanum (Zon. 8.16)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1179 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1165> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1165" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Act. Tr., on Cotta; Cic. Acad. 2.84; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.9.13, on Cotta; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.14, with names confused, cf. 16; see Degrassi 42f., 116, 434f. Both Consuls served in Sicily, captured Thermae Himeraeae and Lipara (Polyb. 1.39.13; Diod. 23.20; Zon. 8.14; cf. Val. Max. 2.7.4, and 9.7; Frontin. Str. 4.1.22, and 30, and 31; Oros. 4.9.13), and Aurelius celebrated a triumph De Poenis et Siculeis (<i>Act. Tr.,</i> Degrassi 76f., 549). On coins of L. Cotta, perhaps celebrating the taking of Lipara, see Grueber CRRBM 1.200f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 (1942) 158." ;
	dprr:hasID 1165 .
